A '''lobster hook''' or '''lobsterhook''' is a hook with a handle (often home-made from a length of thick stiff [[wire]]) used to pull [[crab]]s and [[lobster]]s out of their holes, when [[scuba diving]] or when searching among rocks in the dry at [[low tide]].

