om/modules/ticketing-system/ticket-sharing.swf}}</ref> |- | [[Jira (software)|JIRA]] (from Atlassian) | | Java | Complete | 2011-06-01 |<ref name="YAN2011">{{cite web |first=Steven |last=Yan |title=Setting up and using Zendesk for JIRA Server (OnPremise) |url=https://support.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/203659916-Setting-up-and-using-Zendesk-for-JIRA-Server-OnPremise- |accessdate=2016-05-06}}</ref> |- | [[Node.js]] | | [[JavaScript]] | Incomplete | |<ref name="NODEJS">{{cite web |title=networkedhelpdesk |url=https://www.npmjs.com/package/networkedhelpdesk |accessdate=2016-05-06}}</ref> |}
== Criticism == Harvey Kandola of Countersoft suggested that it would be preferable to have a single application that consolidates all tracking related functions, rather than using multiple tools and "connecting the dots" with initiatives like the Networked Help Desk.<ref name="BRIDGWATER2012">{{cite journal |first=Adrian |last=Bridgwater |title=Countersoft's One-Stop Task and Project Tracker |url=http://www.drdobbs.com/tools/countersofts-one-stop-task-and-project-t/240006917 |date=2012-09-07 |accessdate=2016-05-06 |journal=[[Dr. Dobb's Journal]]}}</ref>
