[[Image:PROVIEW.JPG|thumb|200px|Proview monitor]]
'''Proview International Holdings''' ({{sehk|334}}; {{zh|c=唯冠}}) is a [[Hong Kong]]-based manufacturer of computer monitors and other media devices. The company markets its products under its own and other brand name through its extensive distribution network over the world. Proview manufactures CRT and LCD monitors, LCD TVs, Plasma TVs and DVD players. Proview has production facilities located in [[Shenzhen]], [[Wuhan]] in [[China]], and in [[Brazil]] and [[Taiwan]].
Proview holds the "[[iPad]]" trademark for China and has sued [[Apple, Inc.|Apple]] for [[United States dollar|US$]]1.6 billion in damages.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.macrumors.com/2012/02/13/chinese-authorities-and-retailers-removing-ipads-from-sale-over-trademark-issues/ |title= Chinese Authorities and Retailers Removing iPads from Sale Over Trademark Issues? |last1=Slivka |first1=Eric |date=February 12, 2012 |publisher=MacRumors |accessdate=February 17, 2012}}</ref> Apple has countered that the suit is a shakedown to prop up the company due to its significant debt and impending collapse. Apple ended the dispute paying $60 million to Proview.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://news.cnet.com/8301-13579_3-57379719-37/might-apple-lose-the-ipad-trademark-welcome-to-the-twilight-zone/?tag=txt;title | title = Might Apple lose the iPad trademark? Welcome to the Twilight Zone | first1= Charles | last1= Cooper | publisher = [[CNET]] | date=February 17, 2012 | accessdate=February 17, 2012}}</ref>
